mat = [[Standard-definition television|SDTV]]\n| owner          = [[Mata Amritanandamayi Math]]\n| slogan         = \n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = [[Malayalam]]\n| broadcast area = [[Indian sub-continent]], [[Middle East]], [[Australia]], [[United States]], [[Canada]] & [[Europe]]\n| headquarters   = [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kerala]], [[India]]\n| former names  = \n| replaced names = \n| replaced by names = \n| sister names   = \n| timeshift names  = \n| web           = {{url|http://www.amritatv.com}}\n| sat serv 1    = [[Dish TV]]\n| sat chan 1    = Channel 1913\n| sat serv 2    = [[Reliance Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 2    = Channel 866\n| sat serv 3    = [[Sun Direct]]\n| sat chan 3    = Channel 217\n| sat serv 4    = [[Tata Sky]]\n| sat chan 4    = Channel 1817\n| sat serv 5    = [[Videocon d2h]]\n| sat chan 5    = Channel 610\n| sat serv 6    = [[Airtel Digital TV]]\n| sat chan 6    = Channel 576\n| sat serv 7    = [[DD Free Dish]]\n| sat chan 7    = Frequency: 12729\n| cable serv 1  = [[Kerala Vision Digital TV]] <br /><small>([[India]])</small>\n| cable chan 1  = Channel 041\n| cable serv 2  = [[Asianet Digital]] <br /><small>([[India]])</small>\n| cable chan 2  = Channel 108\n| iptv serv 1    = Anand Media\n| iptv chan 1    = {{url|http://www.anandmedia.tv}}\n| iptv serv 2    = Sling TV International\n| iptv chan 2    = {{url|http://www.sling.com}}\n| iptv serv 3    = Bom TV\n| iptv chan 3    = {{url|http://www.bom.tv}}\n| iptv serv 4    = \n| iptv chan 4    = \n| online serv 1  = Amrita.com/Live\n| online chan 1  = [http://www.amritatv.com/live Watch Live]\n| online serv 2  = \n| online chan 2  = \n}}\n'''Amrita TV''' (Malayalam: \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24 \u0d1f\u0d3f.\u0d35\u0d3f.), was launched in 2005, as a 24-hour Malayalam, general entertainment satellite channel.\n\n==Theme Song==\nThe theme song, \"Lokasamastha,\" was composed by [[Rahulraj]] for [[Mata Amritanandamayi]]'s 50th birthday celebrations in 2003 and later taken as the theme of Amrita TV.\n\n==Current shows==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Title !! Time slot !!Notes!!Year!!Category\n|-\n|Sandhya Deepam||6:25 pm IST(DAILY)||Hosted By Romy Sreekumar ||2005\u2013Present||Devotional Show\n|-\n|Sreshthabharatham||7:00pm IST(Mon-Fri)||Hosted by [[Nithya Das]]||2018- present||Reality Show\n|-\n|Ayyappa Saranam||7:30pm IST(Mon-Fri)||Kaushik Babu , ||2019-Present||serial\n|-\n\n|Kerala Dance League||8:00 pm IST (Mon-Fri)||[[Kaniha|Kanika]], Sreejith Master, [[Bharath (actor)|Bharath]]||2019-Present||Reality Show\n|-\n|Jananayakan||8:00 pm IST (Sat-Sun)||[[Renji Panicker]] , [[Shaji Kailas]]||2019-Present||Talk show\n|-\n|Thonnyaksharangal||9:00 pm IST(Monday to Friday )||Marsheena Neenu,Kavitha Nair, Yedhukrishnan||2019\u2013Present||Serial\n|-\n|Just for fun :Chumma 2||9:00 pm IST (Fri-Sun)||Vimal Pillai,Hrishikesh,Veena Bharath,Kshama Krishnan||2019-Present||Serial\n|-\n|Kadhayallithu Jeevitham||9:30 pm IST(Monday to Friday)||Hosted By [[Vidhubala]]|| 2010\u2013Present||Family show\n|-\n|Annies Kitchen||6:55 pm IST (Sat-Sun)||Hosted By [[Annie (actress)|Chitra Shaji kailas]]|| 2015\u2013Present ||Cookery show\n|-\n|the global indian||10:30 pm IST(Sunday)||rowspan=4 {{N/A}} ||2018-Present||\n|-\n|Nadakame Ulakam||10:30 pm IST(SATURDAY) ||2010\u2013Present||Political Satire\n|-\n|People's Choice||10:30 am IST(SUNDAY)|| 2016\u2013Present||Politics\n|-\n|TOP 10 @10 ||10:00pm IST(Daily)||  2004\u2013Present||NEWS\n|-\n|Malayali Durbar||8:00pm IST(SAT-SUN)||Hosted By [[Tini Tom]]||2014\u2013Present||Talk Show\n|-\n|Arogyavartha||12:30 Noon IST(Daily)|| ||2011\u2013Present||NEWS\n|-\n|''Amruthavarsham''||06:00 am IST(Daily)||rowspan=3|[[Mata Amritanandamayi]]||rowspan=3|2005\u2013Present||rowspan=3|Devotional\n|-\n|''Ammayodoppom''||10:30 am IST (SUNDAY)\n|-\n|''Amruthamgamaya''||06:25 am /06:55 pm IST (MON-FRI)\t\n|-\n|''Udayamritham'' ||06:30 am IST(Daily)|| rowspan=3|TBA||2005\u2013Present (Completed 3,000 episodes)||Motivational/Spiritual\n|-\