{"title_page": "Eluru (Assembly constituency)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=September 2018}}\n{{Infobox Vidhan Sabha constituency\n| name               = Eluru\n| map                =\n| state              = [[Andhra Pradesh]]\n| union_territory    = \n| district           = [[West Godavari district|West Godavari]]\n| electorate         = 238,807\n| year               = \n| reserved           = General\n| mla                = Alla Kali Krishna Srinivas\n| party              = [[YSR Congress Party]]\n}}\n\n'''Eluru Assembly constituency''' is a constituency in [[West Godavari district]] of [[Andhra Pradesh]], representing the [[Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly|state legislative assembly]] in [[India]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ceoandhra.nic.in/ceoap_new/ceo/documents/Electors_Summary%20_25.03.2019.pdf|title=Electors Summary|date=25 May 2019|website=Chief Electoral Officer, Andhra Pradesh|format=PDF|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref> It is one of the seven assembly segments of [[Eluru (Lok Sabha constituency)]], along with [[Achanta (Assembly constituency)|Unguturu]], [[Denduluru (Assembly constituency)|Denduluru]], [[Polavaram (ST)(Assembly constituency)|Polavaram]], [[Chintalapudi (SC)(Assembly constituency)|Chintalapudi]], [[Nuzvid (Assembly constituency)|Nuzvid]] and [[Kaikalur (Assembly constituency)|Kaikalur]].<ref name=\"constituencies22\">{{cite web|url=http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/CurrentElections/CONSOLIDATED_ORDER%20_ECI%20.pdf|title=Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008|date=17 December 2018|website=The Election Commission of India|pages=20, 30|format=PDF|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181003220916/http://eci.nic.in/eci_main/CurrentElections/CONSOLIDATED_ORDER%20_ECI%20.pdf|archivedate=3 October 2018|url-status=dead|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref> ''Alla Kali Krishna Srinivas'' is the present [[Member of Legislative Assembly (India)|MLA]] of the constituency, who won the [[2019 Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly election]] from [[YSR Congress Party]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Assembly Election 2019 |url=http://results.eci.gov.in/ac/en/constituencywise/ConstituencywiseS011.htm |website=Election Commission of India |accessdate=24 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190524074223/http://results.eci.gov.in/ac/en/constituencywise/ConstituencywiseS011.htm |archive-date=24 May 2019 |url-status=dead }}</ref> {{As of|2019|03|25}}, there a total of 238,807 electors in the constituency.<ref name=\"electors\">{{cite web|url=http://ceoandhra.nic.in/ceoap_new/ceo/documents/Electors_Summary%20_25.03.2019.pdf|title=Electors Summary|date=25 May 2019|website=Chief Electoral Officer, Andhra Pradesh|format=PDF|accessdate=24 May 2019}}</ref>\n\n== Members of Legislative Assembly ==\n* 1989 \u2013 [[Nerella Raja]] \u2013 [[Indian National Congress]]\n* 1994 \u2013 [[Maradani Rangarao]] \u2013 [[Telugu Desam Party]]\n* 1999 \u2013 [[P.V.V.P.Krishna Rao (Ambica Krishna)]] \u2013 [[Telugu Desam Party]]\n* 2004 \u2013 [[Alla Kali Krishna Srinivas (Alla Nani)]] \u2013 [[Indian National Congress]]\n* 2009 \u2013 [[Alla Kali Krishna Srinivas (Alla Nani)]] \u2013 [[Indian National Congress]]\n* 2014 \u2013 [[Badeti Kota Rama Rao]] \u2013 [[Telugu Desam Party]]<ref name=\"eci_2014\">{{cite web |title=The Andhra Pradesh Gazette, Part-V Extraordinary |url=http://ceoandhra.nic.in/GE_2014/(GE,%202014)%20-%20DUE%20Constitution%20(APLA_ELECTED%20List).pdf |website=Chief Electoral Officer, Andhra Pradesh |accessdate=13 June 2019 |location=Hyderabad |page=13 |format=PDF |date=20 May 2014}}</ref>\n* 2019 \u2013 [[Alla Kali Krishna Srinivas (Alla Nani)]] \u2013 [[YSR Congress]]\n\n== Election results ==\n=== Assembly Elections 2004 ===\n{{Election box begin | title=[[2004 Andhra Pradesh Legislative Assembly election]]: Eluru}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|\n  |party      = Indian National Congress\n  |candidate  = [[Alla Nani|Alla Kali Krishna 